<br>
Juukak have you parsed it with a level 60 monk?  You may be correct because I have not parsed it so I cannot verify.<br>
<br>
One easy way to tell if item haste stacks with spell haste is for a level 60 monk to remove their item haste.  The difference will be noticable.<br>
<br>
If you have a monk with 36% haste item ( Most monks have at least this much considering how common the Hate Cloak is ) plus the epic haste at 40 percent makes a total of 76 percent with no spell haste added yet.<br>
<br>
A 54-58 monk has a max haste of 84%.  So the 8% diff with spell haste added may not be noticeable.  A 59 monk has max haste of 94%, Difference of 18%... they may notice this.  A 60 monk has 100% haste with a diff of 24 percent.<br>
<br>
Now it is imo that some dipshit monk thinks that when he gets AQ, VOG or whatever which adds 60-65 percent haste looks at it this way.<br>
<br>
Spell haste 65% + Item Haste 36% = 101% (Over max)<br>
Therefore the Epic haste does not stack!!!!  I am just getting AC and Atk bonus!<br>
<br>
Or is it the epic Haste is not Stacking?<br>
<br>
Remove your Item Haste and tell me you lose that 36% haste and the epic haste does not fill the gap with the spell haste.  Are you now at 65% haste only which the spell haste gives?<br>
<br>
Marshall Dashaa<br>
